abstract: Here are some of the stories of how couples, who submitted their announcement information to The New York Times in 2019, agreed to marry each other.
lead_paragraph: An engagement ring hidden in an elephant trunk in Southeast Asia. A golden eagle serving as a wingman for a prospective groom in Mongolia. A double dose of matchmaking magic in Mississippi.
